 Humansdorp - Humansdorp police nabbed two men with stolen goods and also recovered implements used for breaking into vehicles driving a rental vehicle on the N2 highway on Wednesday. "At around 11:30am, it is alleged that two men were seen stealing items from two vehicles that were parked in a fuel station near N2 in Stormsriver," police said. "It is said that the two men (the suspects) then drove away in a silver VW Polo. "A few minutes later, a vehicle was circulated in all police communication channels." Moments later, police spotted a similar vehicle with two men driving on the N2 near Humansdorp and pulled it off the road. "Inside a vehicle, police recovered several goods. A preliminary investigation revealed that the recovered goods were stolen from the two tourists vehicles at the fuel station in Storms River," Humansdorp police said. "Police also recovered a vehicle remote jamming device and other implements that could be used for breaking into vehicles. "A preliminary investigation has revealed that a vehicle that was used was a rental vehicle, but it was fitted with false registration number plates. "The two men, aged 28 and 29, are due to appear in the Humansdorp Magistrate’s Court on Thursday on charges ranging from theft out of motor vehicle to possession of suspected stolen property." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 